726760f-a.title: Queens: Grand Avenue - Simonson Street
726760f-a.text:
Grand Avenue, south side, opposite bleck forred by Simorson and Goldsmith Streets. This honse according to the newly laid out streets is on the west side of Van Horrn Street, which exterds aleng the one and one half story wing of thne house directly in Fifty-second Avenue. It was built by John I Van Alst (1805-1877) about 1845. He married in 1834 Ellen Debevoise. A daughter of .John J. Van Alst occupied this house in 18N2. Isaac 'an Alst (1705-1852) father of John I. married Helen Gorsline and li7d
at Dubh Kills.
1922
